        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><hi rend="italic">Plantago lanceolata</hi> is ribwort plantain. Species that are gynodioecious have hermaphrodite and pistillate (female) flowers on separate plants. In 1878, CD had received specimens of several forms of <hi rend="italic">P. lanceolata</hi> from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3036.xml">Friedrich Ludwig</ref> (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 26, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11534.xml">letter to Friedrich Ludwig, 29 May 1878</ref>). CD added information from Ludwig on the graduated forms of <hi rend="italic">P. lanceolata</hi> to <hi rend="italic">Forms of flowers</hi> 2d ed., p. ix; he did not mention Comber.</note> 
        </div>
    
